<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTD/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- TCC usage descriptions. macOS shows these strings in the
         system permission dialog the first time the app touches the
         corresponding capability. Without them, the OS silently
         refuses access (which is what was breaking the StepNarrative
         dictation button — webkitSpeechRecognition.start() returned
         no error but never delivered results). -->
    <key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Career OS utilise ton micro pour la dictée vocale (étape "Raconte-toi" et autres saisies vocales optionnelles).</string>
    <key>NSSpeechRecognitionUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Career OS convertit ta voix en texte pour pré-remplir ton profil — la reconnaissance vocale s'effectue via Apple Speech.</string>
    <!-- Phase 2 — Core Audio Tap on macOS 14.4+. The OS treats system
         audio capture as a screen-recording-class capability (the tap
         can see what other apps are playing), so it gates it behind
         the screen-capture TCC permission. Without this key, the
         first `tap_desc.create_process_tap()` call returns silently
         empty and the app never appears in System Settings → Privacy
         & Security → Screen & System Audio Recording. -->
    <key>NSScreenCaptureUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Career OS capture la voix de l'interviewer pendant tes entretiens en direct (audio système, jamais l'image de ton écran). Le son sort de Career OS via AssemblyAI puis disparaît — aucun enregistrement n'est conservé sans ton accord.</string>
    <!-- Tahoe (macOS 26) split the legacy "Screen Recording" prompt
         into a dedicated system-audio key. We declare both so the OS
         picks the right one regardless of version. macOS 14-15 will
         ignore the audio key; macOS 26+ will ignore the screen one
         when only audio is requested. -->
    <key>NSAudioCaptureUsageDescription</key>
    <string>Career OS capture la voix de l'interviewer (audio système) pour la transcrire en direct via AssemblyAI. Aucune image d'écran n'est lue ou stockée.</string>
</dict>
</plist>
